[{"id":"p1","text":"<p>What is the area of a circle with radius {r}m?</p>","choices":["<p><code class=\"language-r\">π</code>m</p>","<p><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"open bracket r to the power of 2 close bracket pi\"><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mi>π</mi></span>m</p>","<p><code class=\"language-r\">^2</code>m</p>","<p><code class=\"language-r\">π^2</code>m</p>"],"hints":["<p>Remember that the area of a circle with radius <span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></span> is given by the formula <span class=\"nowrap\"><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"A equals pi r to the power of 2\"><mi>A</mi><mo value=\"=\">=</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></span>.</span></p>","<p>In this case, <span class=\"nowrap\"><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"r equals open bracket 10 close bracket\"><mi>r</mi><mo value=\"=\">=</mo><mfenced open=\"{\" close=\"}\"><mn>10</mn></mfenced></span>,</span> so what do we get for <span class=\"nowrap\"><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></span>?</span></p>"],"variables":null,"read-more":"/course/circles/introduction#area"},{"id":"p2","text":"<p>What is the circumference of a circle with radius 4cm?</p>","choices":["<p><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"4 pi\"><mn>4</mn><mi>π</mi></span></p>","<p><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"8 pi\"><mn>8</mn><mi>π</mi></span></p>","<p><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"16 pi\"><mn>16</mn><mi>π</mi></span></p>"],"hints":["<p>Remember that the circumference of a circle with radius <span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></span> is given by the formula <span class=\"nowrap\"><span class=\"math\" data-voice=\"C equals 2 pi r\"><mi>C</mi><mo value=\"=\">=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mi>r</mi></span>.</span></p>"],"read-more":"/course/circles/introduction#wheel"}]